A meshed surface is drawn with painter's algorithm:

The farest triangles or quadrangles are drawn first.
The nearest are drawn above the farest.
The material seems solid.

Unfortunately, the result is NOT ALWAYS correct.
The computed distance is the distance between the barycentre
of the FE and the eye. A stretched FE may be drawn before
an other farest one.

In this case, use an other view direction.

1 : BLACK and WHITE or COLORS
Drawings with 2 or 256 colors

2 : DRAWING or NOT of FACE EDGES

3 : LINE EDGES COLOR
To define the color of edges if the drawing is requested

4 : DRAWING or NOT of FACES (triangles or quadrangles)

5 : REDUCTION % of FACES
to see better the position of edges of faces
or to see the interior of the materials or the other side

6 : DARKNESS or NOT
The farer faces are drawn with a more darkness color
than the nearest faces or NOT

7 : FACE  NAME COLOR
To define the color of line name if the drawing is requested

8 : DRAWING or NOT of SURFACE NAMES

9 : DRAWING or NOT of the TITLE

10: DRAWING or NOT of VERTEX NUMBERS

11: COLOR of the VERTEX NUMBERS

12: DRAWING or NOT of the FE NUMBERS

13: COLOR of FE NUMBERS

14: SUBDIVISION MAX of an P3 EDGE
With a value from 1 to 15 the drawing of the edge has
a smal or great precision

15: DRAWING or NOT of TANGENTS
at every vertex of a curved Finite Element

16: COLOR of the TANGENTS
To define the color of tangents if the drawing is requested

17: TANGENTS Line Drawing Type
either continue line or dotted line

20: THICKNESS of EDGES
number of pixels into the thickness 0,1, ...

49: AXES of LINES
choose among differents drawings of coordinates axis
 
50: ERASE the WINDOW

75: Activate TRANSLATION ORBIT ZOOM
permit to use the buttons of the mouse after the option 90;
left   button => Translation
middle button => @ in 2D, rotations in 3d
right  button => Zoom + or -

76: Stop the TRANSLATION ORBIT ZOOM
suppress the effect of option 75;

90: EXECUTE the DRAWING
Draw with the drawing characteristics defined before
colors, type of lines, ...
